<TITLE> Cricket season starts with U-18 meet </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 31 (bdnews24.com)  Country's cricket season is all set to get underway in September with the premier division Under-18 teams taking part in the tournament. The U-18 tournament is scheduled for September 20-October 15, according to a calendar designed by the Bangladesh Cricket Board. Before the completion of the U-18 tournament, the National Cricket League will start from October 8 with six divisions playing the country's lone first-class cricket. The Premier Division Cricket League, the most prestigious league at the club level, will roll onto the field from December 27 with its Twenty20 version game. The inter-club cricketers transfer is scheduled for Dec 12-14. The premier division's two-dayers, consisting of 90 overs each side, will start from January 10, 2009 and end on March 25. Afterwards, top six teams from the two-dayer league will take part in the four-dayer matches that are scheduled for 2009 March 27-April 30. The BCB plans to appeal to the International Cricket Council for first-class recognition to the premier division four-dayers. 
